1. In order to install every dependency for an angularJS app type:
	npm install

2. To run angularJS app type:
	npm run start-server
the above mentioned command start a server in http://localhost:3000/app/index.html

If you want to run specific scripts from package.json type:

	npm run <script_name> (scripts available are under scripts key from package.json)

Note that e2e (protractor) needs selenium server up and running for running tests. As such before executing e2e tests type:
	npm run start-webdriver